Note: Runa AWS (Amazon Web Services) Integration Module
Provides comprehensive AWS cloud services management functionality
Following Runa specification patterns with natural language syntax:End Note

Note: Built-in functions are automatically available in Runa programs
Note: No imports required for built-ins like create_runtime_error, execute_command, etc.

Note: AWS EC2 Instance type definition
Type called "AWSInstance":
    instance_id as String,
    instance_type as String,
    state as String,
    public_ip as Optional[String],
    private_ip as String,
    public_dns as Optional[String],
    key_name as Optional[String],
    security_groups as List[String],
    subnet_id as String,
    vpc_id as String,
    availability_zone as String,
    launch_time as Integer,
    tags as Dictionary[String, String],
    monitoring as Boolean,
    architecture as String,
    root_device_type as String

Note: AWS S3 Bucket type definition
Type called "AWSS3Bucket":
    name as String,
    region as String,
    creation_date as Integer,
    versioning_enabled as Boolean,
    encryption_enabled as Boolean,
    public_access_blocked as Boolean,
    policy as Optional[String],
    website_configuration as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    cors_configuration as Optional[List[Dictionary[String, Any]]],
    lifecycle_configuration as Optional[List[Dictionary[String, Any]]],
    tags as Dictionary[String, String]

Note: AWS S3 Object type definition
Type called "AWSS3Object":
    key as String,
    bucket as String,
    size as Integer,
    last_modified as Integer,
    etag as String,
    storage_class as String,
    content_type as Optional[String],
    metadata as Dictionary[String, String],
    server_side_encryption as Optional[String],
    version_id as Optional[String]

Note: AWS Lambda Function type definition
Type called "AWSLambdaFunction":
    function_name as String,
    function_arn as String,
    runtime as String,
    role as String,
    handler as String,
    code_size as Integer,
    memory_size as Integer,
    timeout as Integer,
    last_modified as Integer,
    version as String,
    description as Optional[String],
    environment_variables as Dictionary[String, String],
    vpc_config as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    layers as List[String],
    tags as Dictionary[String, String]

Note: AWS RDS Database Instance type definition
Type called "AWSRDSInstance":
    db_instance_identifier as String,
    db_instance_class as String,
    engine as String,
    engine_version as String,
    db_name as Optional[String],
    master_username as String,
    allocated_storage as Integer,
    storage_type as String,
    storage_encrypted as Boolean,
    vpc_security_groups as List[String],
    availability_zone as String,
    multi_az as Boolean,
    publicly_accessible as Boolean,
    endpoint as Dictionary[String, Any],
    db_instance_status as String,
    creation_time as Integer,
    tags as Dictionary[String, String]

Note: AWS CloudFormation Stack type definition
Type called "AWSCloudFormationStack":
    stack_name as String,
    stack_id as String,
    stack_status as String,
    creation_time as Integer,
    last_updated_time as Optional[Integer],
    description as Optional[String],
    parameters as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    outputs as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    tags as Dictionary[String, String],
    capabilities as List[String],
    rollback_configuration as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]

Note: Execute AWS CLI command with error handling
Process called "execute_aws_command" that takes service as String and command as String and parameters as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let full_command be "aws " with message service with message " " with message command
        For each param in parameters:
            Set full_command to full_command with message " " with message param
        
        Let result be execute_command with command as full_command
        
        If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "aws_command" and context as dictionary with:
                "service" as service,
                "command" as command,
                "parameters" as parameters,
                "exit_code" as result["exit_code"],
                "error_output" as result["stderr"]
        
        Return dictionary with:
            "success" as true,
            "output" as result["stdout"],
            "service" as service,
            "command" as command
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary with:
            "success" as false,
            "error" as error["message"],
            "service" as service,
            "command" as command

Note: Configure AWS credentials and region
Process called "configure_aws" that takes access_key as String and secret_key as String and region as String and output_format as Optional[String] returns Boolean:
    Let config_commands be list containing
    Add "aws configure set aws_access_key_id " with message access_key to config_commands
    Add "aws configure set aws_secret_access_key " with message secret_key to config_commands
    Add "aws configure set default.region " with message region to config_commands
    
    If output_format is not null:
        Add "aws configure set default.output " with message output_format to config_commands
    Else:
        Add "aws configure set default.output json" to config_commands
    
    For each config_command in config_commands:
        Let result be execute_command with command as config_command
        If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "configure_aws" and context as dictionary with:
                "command" as config_command,
                "error" as result["stderr"]
    
    Return true

Note: List EC2 instances
Process called "list_ec2_instances" that takes region as Optional[String] returns List[AWSInstance]:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    If region is not null:
        Add "--region" to parameters
        Add region to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_aws_command with service as "ec2" and command as "describe-instances" and parameters as parameters
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "list_ec2_instances" and context as dictionary with:
            "region" as region,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Let instances_data be parse_json with json_string as result["output"]
    Let instances be list containing
    
    If instances_data contains key "Reservations":
        For each reservation in instances_data["Reservations"]:
            If reservation contains key "Instances":
                For each instance_data in reservation["Instances"]:
                    Let instance be parse_ec2_instance_info with instance_data as instance_data
                    Add instance to instances
    
    Return instances

Note: Parse EC2 instance information from AWS API response
Process called "parse_ec2_instance_info" that takes instance_data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns AWSInstance:
    Let security_groups be list containing
    If instance_data contains key "SecurityGroups":
        For each sg in instance_data["SecurityGroups"]:
            Add sg["GroupName"] to security_groups
    
    Let tags_dict be dictionary containing
    If instance_data contains key "Tags":
        For each tag in instance_data["Tags"]:
            Set tags_dict[tag["Key"]] to tag["Value"]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "instance_id" as instance_data["InstanceId"],
        "instance_type" as instance_data["InstanceType"],
        "state" as instance_data["State"]["Name"],
        "public_ip" as (instance_data["PublicIpAddress"] if instance_data contains key "PublicIpAddress" otherwise null),
        "private_ip" as instance_data["PrivateIpAddress"],
        "public_dns" as (instance_data["PublicDnsName"] if instance_data contains key "PublicDnsName" otherwise null),
        "key_name" as (instance_data["KeyName"] if instance_data contains key "KeyName" otherwise null),
        "security_groups" as security_groups,
        "subnet_id" as instance_data["SubnetId"],
        "vpc_id" as instance_data["VpcId"],
        "availability_zone" as instance_data["Placement"]["AvailabilityZone"],
        "launch_time" as parse_aws_timestamp with timestamp as instance_data["LaunchTime"],
        "tags" as tags_dict,
        "monitoring" as instance_data["Monitoring"]["State"] is equal to "enabled",
        "architecture" as instance_data["Architecture"],
        "root_device_type" as instance_data["RootDeviceType"]

Note: Launch new EC2 instance
Process called "launch_ec2_instance" that takes image_id as String and instance_type as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns AWSInstance:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--image-id" to parameters
    Add image_id to parameters
    Add "--instance-type" to parameters
    Add instance_type to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Note: Add key pair if specified
    If options contains key "key_name":
        Add "--key-name" to parameters
        Add options["key_name"] to parameters
    
    Note: Add security groups
    If options contains key "security_groups":
        Add "--security-groups" to parameters
        For each sg in options["security_groups"]:
            Add sg to parameters
    
    Note: Add subnet ID
    If options contains key "subnet_id":
        Add "--subnet-id" to parameters
        Add options["subnet_id"] to parameters
    
    Note: Add instance count
    Let count be (options["count"] if options contains key "count" otherwise 1)
    Add "--count" to parameters
    Add count to parameters
    
    Note: Add user data if specified
    If options contains key "user_data":
        Add "--user-data" to parameters
        Add options["user_data"] to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_aws_command with service as "ec2" and command as "run-instances" and parameters as parameters
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "launch_ec2_instance" and context as dictionary with:
            "image_id" as image_id,
            "instance_type" as instance_type,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Let launch_data be parse_json with json_string as result["output"]
    If launch_data contains key "Instances" and length of launch_data["Instances"] is greater than 0:
        Return parse_ec2_instance_info with instance_data as launch_data["Instances"][0]
    
    Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "launch_ec2_instance" and context as dictionary with:
        "error" as "No instance data returned from launch"

Note: Terminate EC2 instance
Process called "terminate_ec2_instance" that takes instance_id as String returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--instance-ids" to parameters
    Add instance_id to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_aws_command with service as "ec2" and command as "terminate-instances" and parameters as parameters
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terminate_ec2_instance" and context as dictionary with:
            "instance_id" as instance_id,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Return true

Note: Start EC2 instance
Process called "start_ec2_instance" that takes instance_id as String returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--instance-ids" to parameters
    Add instance_id to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_aws_command with service as "ec2" and command as "start-instances" and parameters as parameters
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "start_ec2_instance" and context as dictionary with:
            "instance_id" as instance_id,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Return true

Note: Stop EC2 instance
Process called "stop_ec2_instance" that takes instance_id as String returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--instance-ids" to parameters
    Add instance_id to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_aws_command with service as "ec2" and command as "stop-instances" and parameters as parameters
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "stop_ec2_instance" and context as dictionary with:
            "instance_id" as instance_id,
